parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Anti-Theft System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: the key gets stuck in the ignition
the key falls out while driving
the anti-theft system light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The anti-theft system glitch can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leaving the driver and passengers stranded, which can be a safety hazard, especially in extreme weather conditions or emergency situations.
symptoms: the engine turns over but won't fire up
the fuel pump is kicking on
the engine will fire up with starter fluid but dies as soon as the fluid burns off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the turn signals can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions to turn, leading to potential collisions.
symptoms: the turn signals stop flashing prior to the physical turn
the turn signals do not initiate at all
